cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.DM, cs.MS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tiling three-dimensional space using tetrahedra, which is a geometric problem.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper deals with visualizing the tiling of space using tetrahedra.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the discrete problem of tiling space using tetrahedra.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category as the paper may involve the development of software to generate and manipulate the tiling of space using tetrahedra.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper may involve the application of game theory to the problem of tiling space using tetrahedra.
